Media24 has announced that it will be launching global media brand Business Insider locally in 2018. The publication will launch in February 2018, Media24 said, and will work alongside its already established Fin24 news group. Business Insider, which has 14 international editions, focuses on international trends and markets, and will track stories around local business innovations. The move to bring over foreign news brands to South Africa follows Media24’s launch of the local edition of Huffington Post in November 2016. Read: The Times print edition set to close  